Recently, the discussion about "village and town merger" has become increasingly heated.
The so-called "village and town merger" means that the residents of natural villages within a certain range are concentrated together to build a new town, and the original land and homesteads are converted into apartment housing property rights at a ratio of 1:1.
Farmers call it "moving upstairs".
However, this measure, which was originally used to support the construction of remote mountainous areas, has been rolled out nationwide. In domestic related discussions, many farmers have expressed their dissatisfaction.

A 60-year-old man died suddenly at his workplace at 3 a.m. at the Ningbo Zhongtong Express sorting center. On the 21st, the Ningbo Community said that 60 years old does not fall into the category of workers, and if work-related injury insurance is not paid, it cannot be recognized as a work-related injury.
A day ago, the official media published an article to promote the re-employment of young elderly people and realize the "silver hair bonus".
